                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the west base of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine, in the Vṛishabhapurīśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Kulōttuṅga I. Year 45: 1114-15 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This fragmentary inscription may be assigned to Kulōttuṅga I on account of the high regnal year. </p>						
                            
                            <p>It records the gift of 32 cows by Paḷḷi Mīṉan <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Villi for a lamp probably in expiation of a sin committed by him for the merit of his wife Irāman Tiruvi. Her brother Irāmaṉ Śaḍaiyaṉ and the <hi rend="italic">Nāṭṭār</hi> assembled and seem to have demanded Villi to provide for a lamp.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
